&lt;p&gt;Thanks to Matt, Jeff, Brad, and Aubrey who all helped in the judging and voting. You guys rock!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="clear:both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://windowsconnected.com/aggbug.aspx?PostID=27888" width="1" height="1"&gt;</description><category domain="http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/joshs_blog/archive/tags/Microsoft/default.aspx">Microsoft</category><category domain="http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/joshs_blog/archive/tags/HP/default.aspx">HP</category><category domain="http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/joshs_blog/archive/tags/BuzzCorps/default.aspx">BuzzCorps</category><category domain="http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/joshs_blog/archive/tags/HPMagicGiveaway/default.aspx">HPMagicGiveaway</category><category domain="http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/joshs_blog/archive/tags/HPMagic/default.aspx">HPMagic</category></item><item><title>IE8 to rely on community for compatibility</title><link>http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/joshs_blog/archive/2008/12/04/ie8-to-rely-on-community-for-compatibility.aspx</link><pubDate>Thu, 04 Dec 2008 19:39:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">6a8e43d9-c7d6-4571-afe6-bea9fc913020:27840</guid><dc:creator>Josh Phillips</dc:creator><slash:comments>0</slash:comments><description>&lt;p&gt;Microsoft is learning that people are very reluctant to update their sites to work correctly with IE8. To help rectify this it will be &lt;a href="http://blogs.msdn.com/ie/archive/2008/12/03/compatibility-view-improvements-to-come-in-ie8.aspx" target="_blank"&gt;relying on the web community&lt;/a&gt; to report sites that have issues with IE8. The report will feed an opt in feature that will automatically update the sites that should render in compatibility mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What isn&amp;#39;t clear from the post on the IE Blog regarding this new opt in feature is what if any performance impact there is for this new feature. I assume the time that this takes will increase as the number of sites reported as requiring compatibility mode increases.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;You will be able to check the number of sites active in the list by placing the following in the address bar - res://iecompat.dll/iecompatdata.xml &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The next IE8 build, which should have this feature, should come out sometime in &lt;a href="http://blogs.zdnet.com/microsoft/?p=1748" target="_blank"&gt;early 2009&lt;/a&gt;. It should also be in the next Windows 7 drop, Beta 1, that is guesstimated at &lt;a href="http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/matt/archive/2008/12/02/windows-7-beta-1-in-1-week.aspx" target="_blank"&gt;Jan of next year&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style="clear:both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://windowsconnected.com/aggbug.aspx?PostID=27840" width="1" height="1"&gt;</description><category domain="http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/joshs_blog/archive/tags/IE8/default.aspx">IE8</category></item><item><title>December 2008 Security Bulletin Notification</title><link>http://windowsconnected.com/blogs/joshs_blog/archive/2008/12/04/december-2008-security-bulletin-notification.aspx</link><pubDate>Thu, 04 Dec 2008 19:22:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">6a8e43d9-c7d6-4571-afe6-bea9fc913020:27838</guid><dc:creator>Josh Phillips</dc:creator><slash:comments>0</slash:comments><description>&lt;p&gt;Next week is patch Tuesday and you won&amp;#39;t be getting the holiday&amp;#39;s off this year.&amp;nbsp; Microsoft will be shipping eight security updates for your patching pleasure.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family:&amp;#39;Verdana&amp;#39;,&amp;#39;sans-serif&amp;#39;;color:#262626;font-size:10pt;"&gt;December 2008 &lt;a href="http://www.microsoft.com/technet/security/bulletin/ms08-dec.mspx" target="_blank"&gt;Security Notifications&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;table style="border-bottom:medium none;border-left:medium none;width:589.5pt;border-collapse:collapse;margin-left:-3pt;border-top:medium none;border-right:med